Finance & Economics Dataset Analysis
📌 Overview
This dataset provides a comprehensive view of financial markets and macroeconomic indicators over time. It combines stock market data with key economic metrics, making it useful for:
🧾 Dataset Description
Each row represents a snapshot of financial and economic conditions for a given date.
📂 Column Description
🗓️ Basic Information
Column	Description
Date	The specific date of the recorded data
Stock Index	The stock market index (e.g., Dow Jones, S&P 500)
________________________________________
📈 Stock Market Data
Column	Description
Open Price	Price of the stock index at market opening
Close Price	Price at market closing
Daily High	Highest price during the day
Daily Low	Lowest price during the day
Trading Volume	Total number of shares traded
________________________________________
🌍 Macroeconomic Indicators
Column	Description
GDP Growth (%)	Economic growth rate of the country
Inflation Rate (%)	Rate at which prices increase
Unemployment Rate (%)	Percentage of unemployed workforce
Interest Rate (%)	Central bank interest rate
Consumer Confidence Index	Measure of consumer optimism
________________________________________
🏛️ Government & Corporate Metrics
Column	Description
Government Debt (Billion USD)	Total government debt
Corporate Profits (Billion USD)	Earnings of corporations
________________________________________
💱 Forex & Commodities
Column	Description
Forex USD/EUR	Exchange rate between USD and Euro
Forex USD/JPY	Exchange rate between USD and Japanese Yen
Crude Oil Price (USD per Barrel)	Price of crude oil
Gold Price (USD per Ounce)	Price of gold
________________________________________
🏠 Market & Economic Activity
Column	Description
Real Estate Index	Performance of real estate market
Retail Sales (Billion USD)	Total retail sales value
Consumer Spending (Billion USD)	Total consumer expenditure
________________________________________
⚠️ Risk & Business Activity
Column	Description
Bankruptcy Rate (%)	Percentage of bankrupt businesses
Mergers & Acquisitions Deals	Number of M&A deals
Venture Capital Funding (Billion USD)	Investment in startups
